article.headline: Montana 92, Montana Tech 63
article.story: BUTTE, Mont. (AP) -- Jake Williams and Casey Briggs scored 14 points each to lead the Montana Tech men's basketball team to a 69-68 victory over Rocky Mountain on Saturday. Sam Conley added 12 points for the Orediggers, Shea Bradshaw had 11, and Tony Trudnowsky had 10, including 2-of-2 3-pointers. Jake Williams grabbed eight rebounds for Tech. The Orediggers led 31-27 at halftime. Elijah Sawn and Alvis Dowiels each scored 12 points for Rocky. Devin Uskoski added 11, and Brian Baker had 10. Dowiels also had 12 rebounds and four assists.
